active people about this...

executive summary: 
in C, checking the boolean value of a pointer is not the same thing 
as checking the boolean value of the thing pointered to. 

git blame points at friedo, but it was broken the same way before his
change in 2013 already, and i cba to look who broke it and when.

and yeah, the patch is against the slightly outdated 0.707, but it is still the same in 
git head, i ran into this on openindiana of all places, so i had to fix various assumptions 
about what is or is not defined at any given time to make it build at all. 
(lack of isinf() in yajl/yajl_gen.c is my favorite really...)

but back to the not-platform-specific wtf.

context for patch:
...
static SV *use_boolean;
...
  use_boolean = get_sv("MongoDB::BSON::use_boolean", 0);
...

--- MongoDB-v0.707.0.0-df2WZ5-ORIG/perl_mongo.c 2014-11-12 21:04:53.000000000 +0100
+++ MongoDB-v0.707.0.0-df2WZ5/perl_mongo.c      2015-02-02 23:23:28.498668962 +0100
@@ -438,7 +438,7 @@
     bool d = bson_iter_bool(iter);
     int count;

-    if (!use_boolean) {
+    if (!use_boolean || (use_boolean && !SvTRUE(use_boolean))) {
       value = newSViv(d);
       break;
     }


and yes, perhaps its more sane to write this as 
    if (!use_boolean || !SvTRUE(use_boolean)) {
because if you end up on the right side of the ||, you kinda already
have checked that it is true/defined/notnull.
but C or XS are not my main languages, so i am a bit conservative there.
and would prefer someone with more clue to really think about this for a moment.
and i really had other plans for tonight than this. (01:02 local here)

so, why doesnt the (existing!) unit test for this catch it? 
because it is broken in the opposite direction.

--- MongoDB-v0.707.0.0-df2WZ5-ORIG/t/types.t    2014-11-12 21:04:53.000000000 +0100
+++ MongoDB-v0.707.0.0-df2WZ5/t/types.t 2015-02-03 00:33:37.108616109 +0100
@@ -284,8 +284,8 @@
     $coll->insert({"x" => boolean::true, "y" => boolean::false});
     my $x = $coll->find_one;

-    isa_ok($x->{x}, 'SCALAR');
-    isa_ok($x->{y}, 'SCALAR');
+    is(ref $x->{x}, '');
+    is(ref $x->{y}, '');
     is($x->{x}, 1);
     is($x->{y}, 0);

i have no idea if there is a better way to phrase "make sure this is a scalar", but
"make sure this is a reference to something inherited from SCALAR" isnt what the test
should do there. because, you know, "boolean" is inherited from "SCALAR" ... GNA-NARF!


so, because i am aware i am ignoring your "how to submit bugreports/patches" pretty
harshly i will pitch in the part i honestly considered "forgetting" about:

	fixing this will change the default behavior of the module.

so perhaps besides fixing the test and the module, the documentation (anything said 
about use_boolean really) needs its logic inverted.
effectively, the default has been for use_boolean to be true for years.
well, and then change the default (back) to 1. (perl_mongo_init in perl_mongo.c)
